sql:
SELECT data_type
FROM model_training_data
WHERE data_id = 1;

SELECT MAX(version1_value) AS peak_accuracy
FROM model_version_comparison
WHERE version1_id = 1 AND metric = 'accuracy';

external_knowledge:
- High-performing model versions refer to those with an f1_score greater than 0.7; 
- Large data files are those with a size greater than 1.0 MB; 
- Recent data files are those uploaded on or after January 1, 2023; 
- The models in question must also have an f1_score greater than 0.8 for the second model.
